args: Please note that this story contains spoilers\nfor chapter 5 of the main campaign\nand the Fractured Futures event.
Hell, someone OPENED me?\nAin't you a weird one!
Might someone explain why this book\nis SPEAKING TO ME?
Might YOU explain why you're runnin'\nyour grubby paws all over my pages?\nLooking for a love spell, maybe? Mmm?

Well, tough luck for you, sister, because
I don't truck with that kind of thing.
But I DO have something else interesting.
Veeeery interesting! Muah ha ha ha!
Several hours earlier, at Cassandra's\nmagical workshop...
I brought you some tea, dearie.\nDrink it down before it goes cold.
Thank you. ...Tsk! Hot! Hot hot!\nI don't think you need worry about\nthis tea getting cold.
So then! To what do I owe the pleasure?
Surely whatever it is could have waited\nuntil my next visit to the castle, mmm?
Or is there some gentleman IN the castle\nwho shouldn't overhear our chatter?\n{player_name}, perhaps? Mmm?
I'm a magical genius, dearie!\nNothing escapes this watchful eye.\nNow then, spill your beans.
You know how His Highness is, yes?\nKind and cheerful... Eager to help...
That's true. He's a model prince—\nnot many boys his age are like that.
But no matter how well he hides it,\nI know the sadness of losing his country\nand family must still burden him.
I can't help but feel His Highness\nis suffering in silence.
I wish to support him. Not just in battle,\nbut emotionally as well.
Th-that is not what I am implying at all!\nHis Highness is my sworn liege lord—\nnothing more or less.
If you say so, dearie. In any case,\nwhy come to me with this?
I hear you once served King Aurelius\nas a court sorceress of sorts.
And that you've known His Highness\nsince he was a child. Which seems\nrather...um...
You think I look too young for that, yes?
And yet, I've rambled this old world\nthree times as long as you, dearie.
Ah ah ah! It's rude to speak of age.\nLet's return to the subject at hand.
It sounds like you think I'll be able\nto advise you in this because I knew\n{player_name} as a child.
But when I left the palace, he was a baby\nnot even knee-high to a grasshopper!
I don't know anything about his life once\nhe started walking and talking and such,\nso I don't know how much help I'll be.
No, the fault is mine for jumping\nto conclusions.
Oh, but I feel terrible turning you away\nwith just a cup of tea after you schlepped\nall this way to see little ol' me...
Say now! Are you a reader?
I enjoy a good book, yes.
Then I have JUST the thing!\nLet me lend you this.
Oh, just a bit of light reading. But be sure\nyou're alone when you open it, all right?
I shall bear that in mind.
Oh! I have some cookies and macarons\nin the pantry. We can have them with\nthe tea.
...Heavens, is that the time?\nI must get back to the castle!
Well, what a fine little party\nwe whipped up here, eh?

It's been a long time since I last sat down
for some tea with a girl a third my age.
I should do it more often! Now where
did I put those hard candies...?
Ahaha...\n(Urrrgh... If she keeps pushing food on me,\nI am likely to burst open right here.)
You know, I've not been part of the prince's\ntroupe for nearly as long as you.
But he's still a special person to me.
All that to say, I'm happy you thought of\nold Cassandra for this little problem.
Yes, well, off you go! Back to the castle\nbefore Cleo gives us both the business\nfor you missing curfew!
Yes, I suppose you're right.\nGood night, then.
Poor child. I don't want her to\nexperience what I did...
I didn't expect her to say His Highness\nwas special to her.
What could she mean by that?\nIs she implying...?
Ah! That book fell from the desk\nand gave me quite the fright!
Oh, this is the one Cassandra gave me.\nThe one I am supposed to read alone.
Well, I certainly seem to be alone now.\nMight as well see what I'm dealing with.
Day 25, Month of the Stardragon\nThe world has Dragonyule fever!
Oh, it's a diary. Goodness, this page\nwas written 40 years ago!
Did you just TURN MY PAGES?\nMuah ha ha ha!
It's me! The book you're holdin'\nin those buttersmooth hands!
I'm sorry. Are you a...talking book?
Look at the big brain on this one! Zing!
And hell, someone OPENED me?\nAin't you a weird one!
Might someone explain why this book\nis SPEAKING TO ME?
Might YOU explain why you're runnin'\nyour grubby paws all over my pages?\nLooking for a love spell, maybe? Mmm?

Well, tough luck for you, sister, because
I don't truck with that kind of thing.
But I DO have something else interesting.
Veeeery interesting! Muah ha ha ha!
...What happened? Is this a castle?\nIt doesn't look like the Halidom.
Where am I?! How did I get here?!
Flustered, eh? Good! Veeeery good!\nMuah ha ha ha ha!

Yep! But I also happen to be a NICE talkin'
book, which is why I'm gonna skip all the
guessin' and riddles and just tell ya that
you're in the palace of Alberia.
...Oh, and it's 40 years in the past.\nProbably should mention that, eh? Zing!
